data.title: Lady Gaga, born Stefani Germanotta, faced persistent bullying during her teenage years in New York City and later at New York University's...
data.meta_description:
2,202 likes, 58 comments - meawwofficial on November 29, 2023: "Lady Gaga, born Stefani Germanotta, faced persistent bullying during her teenage years in New York City and later at New York University's Tisch School of the Arts. Peers targeted her for perceived physical features like her "big nose" and "buckteeth," creating an emotionally challenging environment. Despite the adversity, Gaga pursued her musical aspirations, and her classmates went so far as to create a Facebook page titled 'Stefani Germanotta, you will never be famous' to undermine her dreams.

However, Lady Gaga has defied these expectations and risen to become a highly successful artist. With a net worth of $320 million, she is known for her versatile talent as a singer and actress. Gaga has received critical acclaim, earning 13 Grammy Awards and four Oscar nominations. In 2019, she won the Oscar for Best Original Song for "Shallow" from the movie "A Star is Born," in which she also received a nomination for Best Actress.Beyond her artistic achievements, Lady Gaga has been a vocal advocate against bullying.
